---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - ServerHi">
  <div class="container">
    <article class="legal-page">
      <header class="page-header fade-in-up">
        <h1 class="page-title">
          <span class="terminal-prompt"></span>
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 25, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <!-- Table of Contents -->
        <nav class="toc fade-in-up">
          <h2 class="toc-title">Table of Contents</h2>
          <ol class="toc-list">
            <li><a href="#introduction">Introduction</a></li>
            <li><a href="#information-collected">Information We Collect</a></li>
            <li><a href="#how-we-use">How We Use Your Information</a></li>
            <li><a href="#cookies">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</a></li>
            <li><a href="#third-party">Third-Party Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#data-sharing">Data Sharing and Disclosure</a></li>
            <li><a href="#data-retention">Data Retention</a></li>
            <li><a href="#security">Data Security</a></li>
            <li><a href="#your-rights">Your Rights</a></li>
            <li><a href="#gdpr">GDPR Rights (EEA Users)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#ccpa">CCPA Rights (California Residents)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#children">Children's Privacy</a></li>
            <li><a href="#international">International Data Transfers</a></li>
            <li><a href="#changes">Changes to This Policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact">Contact Us</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="legal-content fade-in-up">
          <section id="introduction" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              ServerHi ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website <strong>serverhi.com</strong> (the "Site").
            </p>
            <p>
              We are a technical education platform providing tutorials and guides on Linux server management, Docker containerization, DevOps practices, and related topics. This policy applies to all visitors, users, and others who access our Site.
            </p>
            <div class="callout callout-info">
              <strong>Quick Summary:</strong> We collect minimal data necessary to provide our educational content. We don't sell your personal information, and we use cookies primarily for essential site functionality and analytics.
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="information-collected" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

            <h3>Automatically Collected Information</h3>
            <p>When you visit our website, we may automatically collect certain information about your device and browsing behavior:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, operating system, device type</li>
              <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages viewed, time spent on pages, referring/exit URLs, search queries</li>
              <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Internet service provider, language settings, time zone, platform types</li>
              <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> General location (country/city) derived from IP address</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
            <p>We may collect information that you voluntarily provide to us:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Contact Forms:</strong> Name and email address when submitting inquiries</li>
              <li><strong>Comments:</strong> Any comments you submit on articles (if feature available)</li>
              <li><strong>Newsletter:</strong> Email address if you subscribe to our newsletter</li>
              <li><strong>Feedback:</strong> Suggestions, questions, or other communications</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How We Collect Information</h3>
            <p>We collect information through:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Direct interactions:</strong> When you fill out contact forms or subscribe to newsletters</li>
              <li><strong>Automated technologies:</strong> Through cookies, log files, and similar technologies</li>
              <li><strong>Third parties:</strong> Analytics providers (see Third-Party Services below)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="how-we-use" class="legal-section">
            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Site Operation:</strong> Provide, operate, and maintain our website</li>
              <li><strong>Improvement:</strong> Improve and personalize your experience</li>
              <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Understand how visitors use our site to improve content</li>
              <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Respond to your inquiries and provide support</li>
              <li><strong>Security:</strong> Detect and prevent technical issues, fraud, and abuse</li>
              <li><strong>Updates:</strong> Send relevant tutorials, updates, and newsletters (with consent)</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="callout">
              <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> We process your data based on our legitimate interest in providing educational content and improving our services, or with your consent for marketing communications.
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="cookies" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
            <p>
              We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our website and store certain information. Cookies are small data files placed on your device.
            </p>

            <h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
            <table class="data-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Category</th>
                  <th>Purpose</th>
                  <th>Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Essential Cookies</strong></td>
                  <td>Required for the website to function properly (theme preference, session)</td>
                  <td>Session / 1 year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Analytics Cookies</strong></td>
                  <td>Help us understand how visitors use our site (Google Analytics)</td>
                  <td>Up to 2 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Functionality Cookies</strong></td>
                  <td>Remember your settings and preferences</td>
                  <td>Up to 1 year</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>

            <h3>Managing Cookies</h3>
            <p>You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy → Cookies</li>
              <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Options → Privacy → Cookies</li>
              <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Cookies</li>
              <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Note: Blocking essential cookies may affect site functionality.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="third-party" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>We may use third-party services that collect, monitor, and analyze data:</p>

            <h3>Analytics</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Analyzes website traffic and usage patterns. <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Advertising</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Google AdSense:</strong> Displays relevant advertisements. <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Hosting & Infrastructure</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Vercel/Netlify/Cloudflare:</strong> Website hosting and CDN services</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="callout callout-warning">
              <strong>Note:</strong> These third parties have their own privacy policies. We encourage you to review their policies for understanding how they handle your data.
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="data-sharing" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do <strong>not sell</strong> your personal information. We may share data only in the following circumstances:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> With vendors who help operate our website (hosting, analytics)</li>
              <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law or in response to valid legal requests</li>
              <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, sale, or acquisition</li>
              <li><strong>Consent:</strong> With your explicit consent</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="data-retention" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain different types of data for varying periods:</p>
            <table class="data-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Data Type</th>
                  <th>Retention Period</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Server Log Files</td>
                  <td>Up to 30 days</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Analytics Data</td>
                  <td>Up to 26 months (Google Analytics)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Contact Form Submissions</td>
                  <td>As long as needed for customer support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Newsletter Subscriptions</td>
                  <td>Until you unsubscribe</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p>We will delete or anonymize your data when it is no longer needed for the purposes outlined in this policy.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="security" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Data Security</h2>
            <p>
              We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal information:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> SSL/TLS encryption for data in transit</li>
              <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Limited access to personal data on a need-to-know basis</li>
              <li><strong>Regular Reviews:</strong> Periodic security assessments and updates</li>
              <li><strong>Secure Hosting:</strong> Use of reputable hosting providers with security certifications</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="your-rights" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
              <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
              <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
              <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to processing of your data for certain purposes</li>
              <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
              <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent for processing based on consent</li>
              <li><strong>Complain:</strong> File a complaint with a data protection authority</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@serverhi.com">privacy@serverhi.com</a>.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="gdpr" class="legal-section">
            <h2>GDPR Rights (EEA Users)</h2>
            <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have additional rights under the General Data Protection Regulation:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> Article 15 - Obtain access to your personal data</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Article 16 - Correct inaccurate data</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Article 17 - "Right to be forgotten"</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> Article 18 - Limit how we use your data</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> Article 20 - Receive your data in a portable format</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Article 21 - Object to certain processing</li>
              <li><strong>Rights Related to Automated Decision-Making:</strong> Article 22 - Not be subject to automated decisions</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Our legal basis for processing personal data includes:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a)) - for marketing communications</li>
              <li>Legitimate Interest (Art. 6(1)(f)) - for analytics and site security</li>
              <li>Legal Obligation (Art. 6(1)(c)) - for tax and accounting purposes</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="ccpa" class="legal-section">
            <h2>CCPA Rights (California Residents)</h2>
            <p>If you are a California resident, you have specific rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Right to Know:</strong> Request disclosure of categories and specific pieces of personal information collected</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Delete:</strong> Request deletion of personal information</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Opt-Out:</strong> Opt out of the sale of personal information</li>
              <li><strong>Right to Non-Discrimination:</strong> Not be discriminated against for exercising these rights</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              <strong>We do not sell your personal information.</strong> Under CCPA, "sale" does not include disclosures to service providers who need the data to provide services.
            </p>
            <p>To exercise your CCPA rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@serverhi.com">privacy@serverhi.com</a>.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="children" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
              Our website is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13 without parental consent, we will take steps to delete that information.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="international" class="legal-section">
            <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>
              Your information may be transferred to and maintained on computers located outside of your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you are located outside the United States and choose to provide information to us, please note that we transfer the data to the United States and process it there. Your consent to this Privacy Policy followed by your submission of such information represents your agreement to such transfer.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="changes" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
              We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Posting the new Privacy Policy on this page</li>
              <li>Updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page</li>
              <li>Providing notice through the Site or email (for significant changes)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="contact" class="legal-section">
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or want to exercise your rights, please contact us:</p>
            <div class="contact-box">
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@serverhi.com">privacy@serverhi.com</a></li>
                <li><strong>General Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@serverhi.com">contact@serverhi.com</a></li>
                <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="/contact">Contact Form</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <p>
              For data protection inquiries, we aim to respond within 30 days.
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* Table of Contents */
  .toc {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .toc-title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--primary);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
  }

  .toc-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.5rem 2rem;
  }

  .toc-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .toc-list li::before {
    content: "›";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .toc-list a {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .toc-list a:hover {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .legal-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .legal-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-section a:hover {
    color: var(--primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-section strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Data Tables */
  .data-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .data-table th,
  .data-table td {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    text-align: left;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .data-table th {
    background: var(--code-bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .data-table td {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .data-table tr:hover td {
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  /* Callouts */
  .callout {
    background: var(--surface);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
  }

  .callout-info {
    border-left-color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
  }

  .callout-warning {
    border-left-color: #f59e0b;
    background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1);
  }

  .callout p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Contact Box */
  .contact-box {
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .contact-box ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .contact-box li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .contact-box strong {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-title {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .toc-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .data-table {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    .data-table th,
    .data-table td {
      padding: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
